==English==

===Etymology===
[Middle English] From Old French ''engin'', which is from Latin ''ingenium'' meaning 'talent, device'. ''Ingenium'' is derived from ''in-'' meaning 'in' and ''gignere'' meaning 'beget'. '''Engine''' originally meant 'ingenuity,cunning' which eventually developed into meaning 'the product of ingenuity, a plot or snare' and 'tool, weapon'.

